sidenote: Fahrenheit to Celsius Converter in CorpoLang
sidenote: use corpolang/src/interpreter.py corpolang/easy_examples/temp_converter.corp to run

sidenote: Define a function to convert Fahrenheit to Celsius
This project, convert_fahrenheit_to_celsius, will have the following deliverables: fahrenheit
    sidenote: Formula: C = (F - 32) * 5/9
    
    sidenote: First, subtract 32 from fahrenheit (F - 32)
    Corporate will assign 'fahrenheit - 32' to adjusted_temp
    
    sidenote: Then multiply by 5 ((F - 32) * 5)
    Corporate will assign 'adjusted_temp * 5' to multiplied_temp
    
    sidenote: Finally, divide by 9 ((F - 32) * 5/9)
    Corporate will assign 'multiplied_temp / 9' to celsius
    
    sidenote: Return the result
    then we'll go live with the celsius

sidenote: Get user input
Corporate will assign 'input("Enter temperature in Fahrenheit: ")' to fahrenheit_input

sidenote: Convert string input to a number
Corporate will assign 'float(fahrenheit_input)' to fahrenheit_value

sidenote: Call the conversion function
Corporate will assign 'convert_fahrenheit_to_celsius(fahrenheit_value)' to celsius_result

